When doing backend security review or writing backend code in this repo, use the
skill defined in `SKILL.md` at the repo root as the source of truth. Read
`SKILL.md` first for the router and mode logic, then open the relevant
`references/*.md` file(s). Review-time produces prioritized findings (severity,
location, CWE + OWASP mapping, fix); write-time applies secure defaults. The
methodology and findings format are in `references/00-methodology-and-severity.md`.

Treat OAuth2/OIDC and social login, API-key lifecycle/scoping, and third-party
security-library vetting as first-class review triggers. Use A07 for auth/API
keys, A03 for the dependency gate, and the security-hardening library index for
dated package dispositions.

Read-only triage scripts are in `scripts/`. Do not rely on this summary alone —
read the referenced files.
